item18.review_text: Conosco personalmente lo staff di RicambiAmericani: team affiatato, sempre pronto ad aiutare con risposte rapide frutto della passione per il loro lavoro e, soprattutto, per le macchine americane.

item23.name: Mauro Savalli
item23.review_text: Pessimo servizio. Dopo numerose richieste, il nulla! Prezzi sopra la media. In Germania, ad esempio, è possibile reperire ricambi Originali a prezzo inferiore.

item25.name: Ben Lee
item25.review_text: Oh to be a Google employee! I had no idea Google was located here until my friend suggested I meet up with him here to discuss something we were to work on. I went in as a guest and went up to the cafeteria where, just like the movie The Intern, everything was free, all the food, just like that. They really have a sublime sense of play here at Google, and an employee here literally has all one could hope for in a workspace that is actually FUN. But of course that means they expect you to work at optimum too, so well done anyone who has managed to be employed here. It is a bit Hogwarts for the doors and corridors you travel around to get to places, but with the colours and features of this place, it cannot be beat.

item26.name: Paul Greening
item26.review_text: Unbelievable the most arrogant organisation I have every dealt with. I eventually got to speak to a real person in Sydney to discuss 2 factually incorrect reviews of my company only to be told I cant speak to anyone. I did mention I followed all their online processes and even contacted the reviewer directly. Great to be a monopoly.

item27.name: Q-LAB Dental
item27.review_text: Front desk contacted for a serious problem (they charged 5K on a not-existing ADW account) very unhelpful and mean. I didn't received any answer from them, they just hung up on me twice.

item28.name: Carolina Darley
item28.review_text: Does anyone actually work at Google? I've been trying for days to call and get the same voicemail message saying office is closed, despite calling during "office hours". I need someone in a managerial position to contact me. The back lens on a 3 month old Google Pixel 2XL self imploded while sitting untouched on a desk. A month ago I was promised by customer support it would be replaced for free. Now that I've returned the phone, Google is denying I was given this information. Online forums show this is happening around the world. This is not user carelessness,this is a faulty product.

item29.name: Lindsay David Watson
item29.review_text: Great place to visit if you get the opportunity. Alas entry is restricted
